text: The Class 185 (branded by its operators as the Pennine Class 185) is a diesel multiple-unit passenger train built by Siemens Transportation Systems in Germany for the British train operating company First TransPennine Express. ==Pictures== Image:First TransPennine Express Class 185 in old livery at York.jpg|185112 at York station in original livery Image:TPE 185139.JPG|185139 Image:Tpenewclass185.jpg|185108 Image:leeds185.JPG|185102 is seen here departing Leeds City station during testing trials on 15 January 2006, and shows the livery in which the trains were delivered.
